							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/priyankamattoo/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/priyanka-mattoo-e1718302410897-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Priyanka Mattoo" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/priyankamattoo/">Priyanka Mattoo</a></h6>
										Priyanka Mattoo is a writer, filmmaker, former talent agent, and a cofounder of Earios, a women-led podcast network. She is the author of <em>Bird Milk & Mosquito Bones</em> and is a contributor to <em>The New York Times</em> and <em>The New Yorker</em>, and a recipient of a MacDowell Fellow­ship. Mattoo holds degrees in Italian and law from the University of Michigan and currently lives in Los Angeles with her husband and kids.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
